Now, for your assumption that there are roving bands of evil manaburners that gate in every time something pops to kill it, I would like to inquire whereabouts you stash your hash pipe. Most of the manaburn &quot;teams&quot; on servers are comprised of Wizards who belong to heavy raiding guilds or are usually busy doing other important things. If you believe that their guild just lets them drop out of a raid to go kill something for money, again I ask where you keep the hash pipe. On most servers the Kunark dragons are up for a day or more before they are killed. These wizards aren't sitting around on the spawn spot waiting for the dragon to pop, there is plenty o time for a guild to mobilize and kill a dragon.<br>
<br>
For the warrior bitching about his epic piece: Manaburn teams are actually dropping the price on Epic scales on the servers. Supply and demand, my friend. With a flood of new supply coming into the market, demand is filled and prices go down. If you absolutely, positively can't get the cash to buy a scale (Maybe you only gouge Sunstrike for 20k pp and scales cost 30k pp), organize your guild and go kill the dragons yourself.<br>
<br>
All this manaburn bitching makes us Wizards irate. <p><P align=center>
